{
  "text": "During that time period, we recruited 18 participants, who were adults with at least one child under age of 18. This is primarily because the HPV vaccine is an adolescent vaccine that is administered between the ages of 11 through 18, and the parent is the decision maker for the child. Each participant was escorted to a private room by the data collector assistant and completed a pre-assessment survey that included basic information about the subject and a Parent Attitudes about Childhood Vaccines (PACV) survey [CITATION_1] that measures vaccine hesitancy. Adjacent to the room, another researcher, the operator, was seated with the desktop application and the dialogue script.",
